      {
         "id": "SECTION_prerequisites",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><span id=\"htAmericaAbyaYalaMsg\"></span> (<htcite0>).</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "160fb48c-1711-491e-a1aa-e1257e7889af",
                     "text": "Porto-Gonçalves, Carlos Walter",
                     "page": "pp. 39-43",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2011",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "### Prerequisites\n\nSubtraction using the *Yupana Inka Tawa Pukllay* method (<htcite0>; <htcite1>) requires prior knowledge of the movements used in addition. Therefore, we recommend studying addition through this method before proceeding (<htcite2>).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "2d2ea4a5-506b-4dbf-aaa4-3a10a8fbbd9c",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit. 2018. Research Gate",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "1bb0274d-dc51-4740-ac62-4d157b06ad88",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team (2024). Yupana (Addition)",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nWe begin studying subtraction by understanding it as a process of return (<htcite0>).\n\nThrough the abacuses, we learned how complements to make 10 can help us perform subtractions, regardless of the magnitude of the numbers (<htcite1>; <htcite2>).\n\nThese studies may indicate how the Incas might have used the Yupana. However, these conclusions may also represent barriers to knowledge. In light of this, we will start with a reflection.",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "73cb1665-6b60-4725-a231-2aff976e7e6d",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Returning",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "00e38f0b-08c9-4833-8857-ae7946d26b74",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Subtracting with Soroban and Suanpan (算盤)",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2026",
                        "month": "07",
                        "day": "16"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a6e475e1-61ff-49d8-9e3a-e508a3facfa7",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Practicing subtraction with Soroban and Suanpan (算盤)",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2026",
                        "month": "07",
                        "day": "16"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: What if we...</b><br /><br />With everything we have seen so far, would it be possible to use the Yupana in a different way?<br /><br />Or did Asians and Incas independently arrive at the same conclusions?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_movements",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Inverse movements with the Yupana\n\nWhen studying addition with the Yupana, we learned five movements used to add numbers using the *Yupana Inka Tawa Pukllay* method (<htcite0>; <htcite1>). In general, these movements, performed with at least two markers, represent a sum that results in another number.",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "1bb0274d-dc51-4740-ac62-4d157b06ad88",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team (2024). Yupana (Addition)",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 2: The reverse</b><br /><br />Do these movements help with subtraction?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "Subtraction on the Yupana is known as *T'aqay*, or parallel subtraction (<htcite0>). This process also uses the movements seen during addition; however, they are performed in reverse order, as we will see next.",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "pp. 360",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### *ISKAY* (inverse)\n\nIn addition, the *ISKAY* movement splits two markers in square 2 into squares 1 and 3. In subtraction, we reverse this: when a marker is in square 3 (value 3) and we need to subtract 1, the inverse movement splits the 3 into squares 1 and 2, then removes the 1, representing the operation",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "pp. 357 - 359",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "1bb0274d-dc51-4740-ac62-4d157b06ad88",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team (2024). Yupana (Addition)",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ":"
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\" style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\" style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\"><p><math mathsize=\"1.5em\" displaystyle=\"false\"><mn>3</mn><mo lspace=\"0.1667em\" rspace=\"0.1667em\">−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo lspace=\"0.1667em\" rspace=\"0.1667em\">=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p></div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "**Table 1** illustrates the inverse *ISKAY* movement. Use the arrow <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-left-right\" style=\"color:#0f0;\"></i> to move the circles, update the fingers, and the arrow <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate\" style=\"color:#00f;\"></i> to return to the original position:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"yupana60\" class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"4\"><i>Yupana</i></th><th>Left Hand</th><th>Right Hand</th><th>Arrows</th></tr> <tr id=\"tf1\"><td id=\"tc1f1\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f1\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f1\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f1\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td><td id=\"tc5f1\"><img id=\"leftHandImg6\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('leftHandImg6', '0%')\"  /></td><td id=\"tc6f1\"><img id=\"rightHandImg6\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('rightHandImg6', '0%')\"  /></td><td id=\"tc7f1\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-left-right upArrowWithFA\" id=\"traineeUp6\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate downArrowWithFA\" style=\"font-size:4em;color:#00f;\" id=\"traineeDown6\"></i></td></tr></table></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Table 1</b>: Inverse <i>ISKAY</i> movement representing <i>3 − 1 = 2</i>. CSS inspired by <htcite0>.</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "48dd9187-7ecc-4f54-a387-d9ecc2497de3",
                     "text": "W3School",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "01",
                        "day": "27"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### *KIMSA* (inverse)\n\nIn addition, the *KIMSA* movement splits two markers in square 3 into squares 1 and 5. In subtraction, we reverse this: when a marker is in square 5 (value 5) and we need to subtract 1, the inverse movement splits the 5 into squares 1 and 3, then removes the extra 1, representing the operation",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "pp. 357 - 359",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "1bb0274d-dc51-4740-ac62-4d157b06ad88",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team (2024). Yupana (Addition)",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ":"
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\" style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\" style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\"><p><math mathsize=\"1.5em\" displaystyle=\"false\"><mn>5</mn><mo lspace=\"0.1667em\" rspace=\"0.1667em\">−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo lspace=\"0.1667em\" rspace=\"0.1667em\">=</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p></div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "**Table 2** illustrates the inverse *KIMSA* movement. Use the arrow <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-left-right\" style=\"color:#0f0;\"></i> to move the circles, update the fingers, and the arrow <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate\" style=\"color:#00f;\"></i> to return to the original position:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"yupana70\" class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"4\"><i>Yupana</i></th><th>Left Hand</th><th>Right Hand</th><th>Arrows</th></tr> <tr id=\"tf1\"><td id=\"tc1f1\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f1\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f1\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f1\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td><td id=\"tc5f1\"><img id=\"leftHandImg7\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('leftHandImg7', '0%')\"  /></td><td id=\"tc6f1\"><img id=\"rightHandImg7\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('rightHandImg7', '0%')\"  /></td><td id=\"tc7f1\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-left-right upArrowWithFA\" id=\"traineeUp7\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate downArrowWithFA\" style=\"font-size:4em;color:#00f;\" id=\"traineeDown7\"></i></td></tr></table></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Table 2</b>: Inverse <i>KIMSA</i> movement representing <i>5 − 1 = 4</i>. CSS inspired by <htcite0>.</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "48dd9187-7ecc-4f54-a387-d9ecc2497de3",
                     "text": "W3School",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "01",
                        "day": "27"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### *PISQA* (inverse)\n\nThe inverse *PISQA* movement is used when we have a marker in the upper line (value 10) and need to subtract 5. The marker is brought down as a single marker in square 5 of the current line, representing the operation",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "pp. 357 - 359",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "1bb0274d-dc51-4740-ac62-4d157b06ad88",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team (2024). Yupana (Addition)",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ":"
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\" style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\" style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\"><p><math mathsize=\"1.5em\" displaystyle=\"false\"><mn>10</mn><mo lspace=\"0.1667em\" rspace=\"0.1667em\">−</mo><mn>5</mn><mo lspace=\"0.1667em\" rspace=\"0.1667em\">=</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p></div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "**Table 3** illustrates the inverse *PISQA* movement. Use the arrow <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-left-right\" style=\"color:#0f0;\"></i> to move the circles, update the fingers, and the arrow <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate\" style=\"color:#00f;\"></i> to return to the original position:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"yupana80\" class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"4\"><i>Yupana</i></th><th>Left Hand</th><th>Right Hand</th><th>Arrows</th></tr> <tr id=\"tf1\"><td id=\"tc1f1\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f1\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f1\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f1\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td><td id=\"tc5f1\" rowspan=\"2\"><img id=\"leftHandImg8\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('leftHandImg8', '0%')\"  /></td><td id=\"tc6f1\" rowspan=\"2\"><img id=\"rightHandImg8\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('rightHandImg8', '0%')\"  /></td><td id=\"tc7f1\" rowspan=\"2\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-left-right upArrowWithFA\" id=\"traineeUp8\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate downArrowWithFA\" style=\"font-size:4em;color:#00f;\" id=\"traineeDown8\"></i></td></tr> <tr id=\"tf2\"><td id=\"tc1f2\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f2\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f2\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f2\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td></tr></table></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Table 3</b>: Inverse <i>PISQA</i> movement representing <i>10 − 5 = 5</i>. CSS inspired by <htcite0>.</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "48dd9187-7ecc-4f54-a387-d9ecc2497de3",
                     "text": "W3School",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "01",
                        "day": "27"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### *PICHANA* (inverse)\n\nIn addition, the *PICHANA* movement sweeps markers together from squares 1 and 2 into square 3. In subtraction, we reverse this: when a marker is in square 3 (value 3) and we need to subtract 2, or in square 3 (value 3) and we need to subtract 2, or in square 2 (value 2) and we need to subtract 1, the inverse movement splits the 2 into two markers in square 1, then removes one, representing the operation",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "pp. 357 - 359",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "1bb0274d-dc51-4740-ac62-4d157b06ad88",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team (2024). Yupana (Addition)",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ":"
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\" style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\" style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\"><p><math mathsize=\"1.5em\" displaystyle=\"false\"><mn>3</mn><mo lspace=\"0.1667em\" rspace=\"0.1667em\">−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo lspace=\"0.1667em\" rspace=\"0.1667em\">=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math mathsize=\"1.5em\" displaystyle=\"false\"><mn>2</mn><mo lspace=\"0.1667em\" rspace=\"0.1667em\">−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo lspace=\"0.1667em\" rspace=\"0.1667em\">=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p></div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "Select the inverse *PICHANA* movement using the options above, then use the arrow <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-left-right\" style=\"color:#0f0;\"></i> to see the result, and the arrow <i class=\"fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate\" style=\"color:#00f;\"></i> to return to the original position:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
