               "text": "### Cancellation\n\nAn important concept in subtraction with the Yupana is **cancellation**. If two markers of the same color occupy the same square, they represent the same value being added and subtracted, canceling each other out. This is because any number subtracted by itself equals zero. This principle is especially useful when simplifying calculations during subtraction.",
